</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="80.[151,1436,330,836]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis box="[198,301,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species is known only from the male 
<typeStatus box="[836,942,690,716]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">holotype</typeStatus>
, and is the second of only two species of Neotropical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1899" box="[296,439,730,755]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Dasymutilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[296,439,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Dasymutilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that we have not examined. Its placement in the key is based on the original description by 
<bibRefCitation author="Suarez, F. J." box="[254,429,770,796]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" pagination="169 - 188" refId="ref97136" refString="Suarez, F. J. (1970) Datos sobre mutilidos neotropicales, VII: Algunes especies del Peru representadas en las colecciones del Museo de Historia Natural de Basilea (Suiza) (Hymenoptera). Arch. Inst. Acl. Almeria, 15, 169 - 188." type="journal article" year="1970">Suarez (1970)</bibRefCitation>
, who stated that “this could very well be the male of the previously described 
<taxonomicName box="[151,454,810,835]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Dasymutilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="homochroma">
<emphasis box="[151,454,810,835]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Dasymutilla homochroma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, ... captured in the same locality at the same time.”
</paragraph>
